SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: CHARGERS SIGN ONE ROOKIE, RELEASE ANOTHER 
The Chargers signed Greg Lewis, a rookie free agent wide receiver, and released 
rookie free agent linebacker Mike Matthews on Friday. 
Lewis is a 5-foot-9, 157-pounder who was a member of Texas A&amp;M's 1987 
All-American sprint relay team. He didn't play football his senior year and saw 
limited playing time on special teams and at receiver as a junior. 
Matthews attended Oregon State. 
COLLEGE BASKETBALL 
U.S. International University has named Jack Murray an assistant basketball 
coach. He was a part-time assistant a year ago. 
Murray will replace Steve Kinder, who left USIU two weeks ago for the head 
coaching position at Oceanside High School. 
